# TimeWise Tracker – Project Context

TimeWise Tracker is a **Next.js 15** time-tracking app with **Firebase** (Firestore, Functions, App Hosting) and **Stripe**. It supports individual and team tracking with subscription management.

## Requirements

- **Node.js 22** – `package.json` enforces it. Do not use older versions.
- **Key commands before commit:** `npm run format`, `npm run lint`, `npm run functions:lint`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm test`

## Pull requests

- **Always** use `.github/pull_request_template.md` when creating PR descriptions.
- Use the **Create Pull Request** task in `.cursor/tasks/create-pull-request.md` to generate a description from the template.
- Compare against `origin/main` when describing changes.

## Conventions

- **Commits & PR titles:** conventional commits only: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `style:`, `refactor:`, `perf:`, `test:`, `build:`, `ci:`, `chore:`, `revert:`. Required for semantic-release.
- **i18n:** All user-facing text goes through `next-intl`. No hardcoded UI strings. Every key must exist in **en, de, and es** (`src/messages/{en,de,es}/`). See `.cursor/rules/i18n.mdc` and `docs/i18n-setup.md`.

## Structure

- `src/app/` – Next.js App Router
- `src/components/` – React components (incl. `ui/`, `team/`)
- `src/lib/` – utils, Firebase, auth, time helpers
- `src/hooks/`, `src/services/` – React hooks and API/Firebase services
- `functions/` – Firebase Cloud Functions
- `e2e/` – Playwright E2E tests
- `docs/` – project docs

